Parents/Guardians of K-6 full Cyber (CAOLA) students.



There will be 3 informational meetings held VIA zoom on September 9th 2020.

During those meetings we will discuss expectations and answer questions.

Your student will start using CAOLA officially on September 14th. They will be able to pick up their Chromebook on the 8th or 9th of September in their home school office. Their teacher will be reaching out to them in the days to come to introduce themselves.



Attend one of these meetings using the link and the ID and code found below. All three meetings will have the same information, we wanted to be mindful of busy work schedules, so we planned 3.

September 9th, 2020 9:00 AM meeting

September 9th, 2020 4:00 PM meeting

September 9th, 2020 8:00 PM meeting

2021 Seniors,

Students who are planning to attend college, here is an update on local SAT and ACT test dates and Registration:

Please watch the DEADLINES to register. It will be very important to test early since many of you did not have a junior spring test score so you will be ready for college apps come fall/early winter.

SAT's Test Date Location Registration Deadline

Aug 29 @ MASH July 31

Sept 26 @ CASH Aug 26

Oct 3 @ MASH Sept 4

ACT Sept 12 @ MASH Aug 14

Oct 24 @ MASH Sept 18



Please email mflinchbaugh@csddrive.org if you need any help creating accounts on www.collegeboard.org for SAT or www.actstudent.org for ACT or for Fee Waivers for those students who qualify.

If you have any further questions please contact John Acklin at john.acklin@conneautsd.org or your athlete's coach!

post_text:
Graduation recordings will take place on June 1, 2, 3, and 4 (Monday through Thursday). The videoing has changed slightly; now they will occur in the main lobby at CASH and be done in front of the Eagle statue. Filming will begin at 9 am and conclude at 4 pm each day. Each filming should take approximately 10 minutes.

A signup sheet will be available during cap and gown distribution for seniors to pick a day and time to be filmed. Seniors will still bring any school materials they need to return on the day that they signed up for. There will be a maximum of 38 filmings per day

Each graduate will be allowed to have up to 8 immediate family members in attendance for the filming. All social distancing guidelines will be followed during your time inside the school building.

Any questions please contact Mr. Wertelet at jwertelet@conneautsd.org or Mr. Morris at cmorris@conneautsd.org

The district just received word from the PA Department of Education that we are now closed through April 6th for staff and April 8th for students. Students at this time would report back to school on April 9th. We realize this is supposed to be the start of Easter break, however, at this time we don’t know that Easter break will proceed as planned. All school districts in the Commonwealth will be instructed on “Continuity of Education” tomorrow, March 24th. After that meeting we will have a better idea what the PA Department of Education would like us to attempt over the remaining days that have been scheduled off. As directions and instructions come from PDE and the Governor's office, we are making every effort to keep our families updated and informed. Updates will follow as we learn more.
Thank You

post_text: Upon further consideration, we at the Crawford Heritage Community Foundation have decided not to delay our scholarship application deadlines. We acknowledge, however, that we must be flexible when it comes to the required documentation. If it is easier, please feel free to send me electronic versions of your students' transcripts and recommendation letters. Students may submit their documentation to me electronically as well. Also, please reassure students that if they are unable to attain all three letters of recommendation, are only able to provide unofficial transcripts, or are not able to provide an otherwise required document to us, they should still apply. We will still consider their application materials for scholarship awards with the materials they are able to provide us. Whitney Swance Starczewski <whitney@crawfordheritage.org

post_text:
Conneaut School District will be closed for 10 business days
Dear Conneaut School District Staff and Families

By now, you have most certainly seen the directive from Governor Wolf in closing all of PA schools. We will be closed for two weeks, and at this time, resume classes on march 30th. This could of course change depending on where we are as a country at that point. We have been told that we will not have to make the days up. Central Office employees, Principals, Full time Secretaries, Maintenance and Technology Departments will continue to work throughout the closure. Additionally, Cafe employees will be working as we will continue to get meals out to students. We are working on plans for meal delivery now. As we learn more, we will continue to contact you through email and phone.

Please help each other out and take care of elderly family and neighbors as they are most at risk.

post_text:
Good afternoon
,
Wanted to provide an update on Edinboro RCI classes.
At this time, the spring break will be extended through March 16th.
Tentatively, RCI professors will have face-to-face classes at the RCI sites starting March 23.
Even though college students going to the EU campus will have class on-line, we are working with the University to have face to face classes with RCI students since the high schools are open and classes are off-site.
We will keep you updated as the plan is finalized.

post_text:
The CASH Drama Club is venturing into the Hundred Acre Wood this spring as they present the classic show “Winnie-the-Pooh.” Beloved by all ages, Pooh’s simplicity and kindness is something our world could really use.

Do you want to be part of the show? Actors and crew are all needed for the show. If you’re in 9th or 10th grade and want to learn the light and sound board, make sure to see Mrs. Morris.

Audition packets are required for anyone who wants to be onstage portraying a character. Stop in Room 107 to pick up a packet and sign up for an audition time. You can also find the audition packet on the CASH Drama Club Canvas Page. Not a member of the page? See Mrs. Morris for help!

SUPPORT PROFESSIONAL VACANCY

Special Education Secretary for ACCESS

February 13, 2020

POSITION DESCRIPTION: Full time, 260 days/year (8 hours/day) located at Central
Office Administration Building.

JOB SUMMARY: Assist the Director of Student Services and Administrative Assistant to the Director of
Student Services in the operation of the district Special Education department including
ACCESS billing.

*QUALIFICATIONS:
 High School Diploma or equivalent
 One (1) year minimum experience as a secretary and/or in data entry/technology in public education or the public sector preferred
 Competence in specialized areas of technology

SALARY: Beginning at $16.54/hr

DEADLINE FOR APPLICATION: February 28, 2020

PROCEDURE: Submit a letter of interest, resume, current Act 24, 34, 114 & 151 clearances and
3 letters of recommendation to:
Conneaut School District
Sue Larson, Confidential Personnel Secretary
219 West School Drive
Linesville, PA 16424

Job Description to be made available upon request.

post_text:
Pennsylvania Music Educators Association (PMEA) District 2 Chorus Festival – one of 12 District Chorus festivals around the state this weekend.
District 2 consists of seven counties: Erie, Crawford, Warren, McKean, Elk, Potter, Cameron
This year’s choir consists of 200 singers from 38 schools.
The guest conductor is Ken Myers, recently retired choral director at Port Allegany HS.
• Concert is at 2:00 pm Saturday in the CASH auditorium. Admission is $4 for adults, $3 for students.

The NRA Youth Education Summit is now accepting applications
for the 2020 Youth Education Summit. Current high school sophomores and juniors are eligible to apply. Admitted students receive an expense-paid week in the Washington, D.C. area with the chance to earn up to $50,000 in college scholarships.

The summit offers a unique opportunity to learn more about American history, government, and the NRA while making friends with other students from all over the country. Don’t miss out on the experience of a lifetime.
Talk to guidance for help applying.
DEADLINE: JANUARY 24, 2020

“We are such stuff As dreams are made on, and our little life
Is rounded with a sleep.”
If you dream of crafting Shakespeare’s work into your own, consider joining the Shakespeare Team for the Thiel College Shakespeare Festival. The Festival is scheduled for January 30 and will take place during the school day.
This year all schools will be working with scenes from The Tempest.
Please contact Mrs. Morris ASAP if you would like to join the team. Casting needs to happen soon so that there is time to memorize parts.

The Conneaut Area Music Dept. is proud to announce the results from the 2019 PMEA District Jazz Auditions at Youngsville HS last night. Everyone that auditioned did very well and the staff is extremely proud of everyone that participated.

Congratulations to the following students who auditioned and qualified for the 2020 PMEA District Jazz Festival to be held in February at Bradford Area High School:

In BAND 4:
Abby Stine – Tenor Sax 1
Rachel Gillette – Trombone 2

In BAND 3:
Steven Lasch – Alto Sax 2
Bret Labonowski – Trumpet 4

And finally in BAND 1:
Quinn Cameron – Tenor Sax 1
Travis Butterfield – Trumpet 1
Kameron Langford – Bass Trombone
Tim Barnes – Lead Guitar
Nathan White – Vibraphone

It was a great night for Conneaut Area with 9 students qualifying for the festival in February. Again, the music staff is very proud of everyone that auditioned. Please be sure to congratulate everyone when you see them today.
